# Git Branching & Timesheet App Updates

This plan covers the transition to a branching workflow and the implementation of the first set of updates from the user's task list.

## 🌳 Git Branching Workflow

We will move away from committing directly to `main`. Instead, we'll use a feature-branch approach.

1.  **Create Branch**: `git checkout -b updates-v2`
2.  **Develop**: Make changes to the code in this branch.
3.  **Local Test**: Open the local `index.html` (or use a local server) to verify changes on your computer.
4.  **Mobile Test**: 
    - We will look into [Firebase Hosting Preview Channels](https://firebase.google.com/docs/hosting/test-preview-deploy) if the app is hosted on Firebase.
    - Alternatively, we can use a local IP address to test on your phone over Wi-Fi.
5.  **GitHub Push**: `git push origin updates-v2` (keeps the work backed up in the cloud).
6.  **Merge**: Once all 15 tasks (or a logical subset) are done and tested, we'll merge `updates-v2` back into `main`.

## 🧪 Testing Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A (Standard web app testing using the browser tool for UI checks).

### Manual Verification
- **Local Browser**: Refresh `index.html` after ஒவ்வொரு change.
- **Mobile Check**: Access via local IP or Firebase Preview URL.
- **Offline Test**: Task #7 ("run test entering data offline") will require disabling the network in the browser dev tools.

## 🛠️ Proposed Changes (Initial Batch)

We will start with the first few visual and data-sync adjustments:
- [ ] Task #1: 12hr time format in sync data.
- [ ] Task #2: Change pay date/period font size to 18pts.
- [ ] Task #3: Define a visible grid.
- [ ] Task #4: Reduce rows from 39 to a smaller number.

> [!NOTE]
> We will create the `updates-v2` branch first before making any of these changes.
